<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 618<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/02 11:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1663.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: GUILD ADVICE</span><hr size=1> Well, its actually in pretty poor taste to apply to two guilds at the same time.  Basically you're saying, I don't really care whether or not I get into your guild, I'm just looking to get into any guild.  It comes across as kind of self serving, to be honest.<br>
<br>
And given the greed, envy, childish behavor, and aggravation a bad choice can bring to a guild, its kind of hard to blame them for wanting to be as careful as they can.<br>
<br>
Edit: Oh and by bringing your dirty laundry here to a public forum you've actually pretty well validated their decision.  It tends to show you would probably have been a bit over dramatic for the health and well being of most guilds. <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A> at: 12/5/02 11:08:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tongpo@thesteelwarrior>Tongpo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/02 12:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1663.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: GUILD ADVICE</span><hr size=1> &quot;Edit: Oh and by bringing your dirty laundry here to a public forum you've actually pretty well validated their decision. It tends to show you would probably have been a bit over dramatic for the health and well being of most guilds. &quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
This is the tavern after all or is it not a place to discuss such things? If you made a mistake that cost you membership into two great guilds im sure you'd be pretty pissed off as well. Im not here talking smack about either of the guilds. Im just here venting my frustration. Not everyone has the experience and knowledge that you do when it comes to getting a guild. I posted here to warn people that, like myself, are new to this so they wont make the same mistake I did. One of the greatest gifts EQ can provide is the satifaction of helping and guiding others. Some of us tend to forget that and get so caught up with ourselves the we step on those that may not be of the same experiance lvl. Honest mistakes do happen. As far as me being overdramatic is concerned, I chose a tone and demeanor to show that I repect them and I respect any decision they make. If I were to be dramatic and childish, which is what they dont want, I would have pitced a fit, cursed, and had myself banned. But where exactly would that get me? Aboslutely nowhere. <br>
<br>
<br>
Tongpo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 620<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/02 1:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1663.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: GUILD ADVICE</span><hr size=1> Well, lets discuss this.  Maybe I'm mistaken.  Didn't you add a link to the bottom of your initial thread leading to a guild board?  Don't you thereby indicate at a minimum which guild in all probability showed you the door when they found out you were applying to more than one guild?<br>
<br>
I would conclude from this that not only are you telling people that its a bad idea to apply to two guilds at the same time, which is very good advice, but you're going out of your way to identify the guild that shut you out.  Why?<br>
<br>
Why does anyone who might need your advice on not applying to two guilds need the link?  It leads me to conclude that somehow you wanted to bring attention to this guild for some reason.  Certainly it wouldn't be to commend them on their fine application process, would it?<br>
<br>
